# Constitution — {{PROJECT_NAME}} (workspace)

> **Binding.** Shared rules for the whole monorepo. `AGENTS.md` describes *how to work*; this
> file defines *what is always true everywhere*. Stack-specific rules live in
> `constitutions/<area>.md` — read the one for the repo you are touching. On conflict, the
> area file narrows within its stack; this file governs everything shared.
> Never archived, always in context. Changing a rule is a deliberate amendment — date it.

## Members

Each member repo has its own stack rules in `constitutions/<area>.md`. `WORKSPACE.md` is the
registry of areas → paths → stacks. Membership is explicit there; nothing is auto-discovered.

## Prohibitions — process

- **Never auto-commit.** Update files, report what changed, let the user decide.
- Never mark a feature ✅ without evidence recorded in `FEATURES.md`.
- **One feature (row) active at a time per person** — the atomic unit is a `FEATURES.md` row,
  not the story/epic it belongs to. A cross-area story is worked one row at a time; it is done
  when all its rows are ✅. Out-of-scope ideas become new rows, not drive-by edits.

## Git

- Base branch for PRs: `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`. Feature branches: `{{BRANCH_PATTERN}}`.
- **Commit messages are prefixed with the feature ID:** `{{FEATURE_ID_EXAMPLE}}: <summary>`.
  This lets `git log --grep="<id>"` corroborate the `By` column in `FEATURES.md`.
- One `.git` at the workspace root governs every member (monorepo). A single commit may touch
  more than one area.
- **State is one file per person:** `state/<git config user.name>.md` — at the workspace root,
  never per member. You write only your own file; nobody else touches it, so merge / rebase /
  cherry-pick stay conflict-free by construction.
- **Cross-person visibility lives in `FEATURES.md`, not in state files.** Its `Area` column
  tells you which member each in-flight row touches.
- Attribution comes from `git config user.name` on the machine running the session — never from
  the agent, so it works identically for any tool.

